cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with improving the Stochastic Neighbour Embedding algorithm, which is commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of a data-dependent kernel, which is relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
